byline.contributor: Yamiche Alcindor and Thomas Kaplan contributed reporting.
byline.original: By AMY CHOZICK and PATRICK HEALY

abstract: Associated Press survey says that Hillary Clinton has secured enough superdelegates to win Democratic presidential nomination, becoming first woman to lead national ticket of major political party; her rival Bernie Sanders has vowed to continue his candidacy until convention.
lead_paragraph: On the eve of the New Jersey and California primaries, an Associated Press survey of superdelegates indicated that Mrs. Clinton had gone over the top.

headline.main: Hillary Clinton Has Clinched Democratic Nomination, Survey Reports
headline.print_headline: Clinton Reaches Historic Mark, A.P. Says
